#Text=Yes , mainly the left side .
#Text=Any reason for that ?
#Text=No , there 's no reason .
#Text=We just never know how NF is gon na affect anyone .
#Text=Everything on the left side accept the arm .
#Text=The arm has a lot of strength and is not disfigured in any way .
#Text=The daily life of Reggie Bibbs
#Text=Reggie having fun with Beyoncé Knowles in April 2007 .
#Text=Image : Greg Gorman .
#Text=What 's a regular day in your life like ?
#Text=A regular day for me starts off with waking up in the morning and taking care of my leg .
#Text=There are a few areas that really need treatment , special dressings for it , and after I , you know , wash and dress that area and then I go through the difficult task of putting the sock on .
#Text=So I have to really work hard with this sock with a net on and after that everything else goes on .
#Text=And I have to work on my eyes , I have to wash it when I wash and put my eye ointment in .
#Text=And then after that it 's basically doing what everyone else does with the exception of ...
#Text=I do a lot for my family so I 'm doing a lot for them which I do n't mind .
#Text=I 'm happy to help .
#Text=That 's basically how it starts .
#Text=And I usually go to the grocery stores and things like that in my area , where people know me .
#Text=They are nice there .
#Text=Is it hard for you going outside your area ?
#Text=It 's really hard for me to go to a store that 's not in my area .
#Text=It 's like there 's a boundary to where I stay inside of that boundary .
#Text=There 's only certain stores in the area that I would go to and if I 'm on the other side of town
#Text=if I need something I wo n't go to a store where people are not used to seeing me .
#Text=I just do n't want to create problems , I do n't want to shock anyone or hurt anyone or I do n't want to be hurt .
#Text=So I just do n't feel comfortable into going into stores that I 'm not accustomed to be going to .
#Text=What kind of bad experiences have you had ?
#Text=Well , there are some bad experiences where I walk up to a door , some people will lock the door and wo n't let me in .
#Text=Some people will just turn and go the other way or cover their face or just shy away from me .
#Text=How does that make you feel ?
#Text=It makes me feel angry because it makes me feel like I know they know better but they 're doing it to be mean .
